{
  "texts": [
    "For each parameter we ran LMEs (with the covariates mentioned above) that compared the three task conditions by group.",
    "Given our transdiagnostic focus, we first divided participants into two groups comprised of healthy participants and those diagnosed with one or more psychiatric disorders (transdiagnostic group).",
    "We subsequently divided those with psychiatric diagnoses into the 5 distinct diagnostic groups to assess the potential for diagnosis-specific differences.",
    "To test the relative evidence for models with vs. without group and condition effects, we ran JZS Bayes factor analyses with default prior scales in R [85, 86] comparing null models (with only an effect of subject) to the space of models including all combinations of main effects and interactions for group and condition.",
    "We also compared evidence for models with transdiagnostic vs. condition-specific effects."
  ]
}